I've been going here because it is conveniently close to where I live.
It nice to go to a place to practice for the bigger fields.
You have your mix of pro, semi and amateur players.
So you can definitely can get better as a player and still have fun.
This place is great for kids.
They have great accommodation for kids here.
You have the option to shoot 50cal paintball which hurts a lot less.
The prices are very reasonable.
You can play here for under 50 bucks.

This was my first time paintballing but Fridays are only $10 for girls (includes 100 paint balls).
the staff was super nice and welcoming.
Also when our bag of 500 paint balls went missing, they replaced it for free.
Also, if you bring your Friday  or Saturday receipt back on Sunday, you can play for free.
What a good deal!
Overall the atmosphere was good and the arena was interesting as well.
The games played were: 5 minute respond and medic.

