Indoor paintball experience, interesting!
This was my second time playing paintball, and man was I scared.
Last time I played was probably 6 years ago and it was outside.
I had all the gears and pads since I borrowed it from a friend.
I was basically padded up unlike when I played it the second time.
Boyfriend bought a Groupon deal, so it wasn't expensive at all, and plus he had gears of his own, enough for the both of us to use, so heck yes!
Make sure you watch the safety video!
It's important even if you are not paying much attention to it.
Make sure to protect your face with the mask.
NEVER take it off when you are in the game.
The workers here will let you know when the next game starts and when it ends.
Each game is about 15 min long.
Make sure you wear clothes that you don't care and shoes that doesn't have holes.
During the game, the floor gets slippery because of the paint balls, so I would suggest to be careful not to slip.
Game players here are nice and most people come here as family and friends, so mostly in groups.
If you come here with your friend, girlfriend or just boyfriend, you have yourself an awesome partner in crime or one bad ass couple!
Will come back when it's not too hot.
Bring your own snack and drinks!
They do have lockers and benches for you to leave things there and to sit after a game.
I hope to play here again!

Came here for a friend's birthday and it was pretty interesting.
Playing indoor is a lot more difficult than outdoors from my experience.
There's not as much room and it's harder to find good hiding spots.
They had a few good barrels and sheds to hide behind but there just wasn't a lot of space to run around.
So I got shot a lot more than at the outdoor one I've been to.
The games were odd, can't remember the names but you could respawn in one and another one you had to stay inside a house for a designated period of time and it was impossible not to get shot up.
The games went so fast and then we had to wait a while for until we could get into another game so we spent a lot of time sitting around.
The floors are incredibly sticky from all the paint, I felt like it was a struggle to take each step.
They also had to caution tape a part of the field because something fell off the ceiling and exposed dangerous edges.
I prefer taking the long drive to North Scottsdale for splatter ranch for the large outdoor paintball setting than the small indoor at Tempe Paintball.

